# Implementation Plan - Phase 1: UX & Core Polish

## Goal
Transform the current fitness tracker into a modern, premium web application with a "Glassmorphism" design, responsive mobile navigation, and an interactive dashboard.

## User Review Required
> [!IMPORTANT]
> This plan involves significant UI changes. The existing "minimalist" or "default" look will be replaced by a dark, glassmorphism-inspired theme.
- **Theme**: Dark mode by default with vibrant accent colors (Blue/Purple gradients).
- **Navigation**: Mobile-first bottom navigation bar. Desktop will reuse the same logic but in a sidebar or top bar.
- **Charts**: Integrating `Recharts` for data visualization.

## Proposed Changes

### Client

#### [MODIFY] [tailwind.config.js](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/client/tailwind.config.js)
- Extend theme colors to include "glass" utilities and custom color palette.
- Add background image or gradient configuration.

#### [MODIFY] [index.css](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/client/src/index.css)
- Add base styles for the dark theme background.
- implement custom `.glass` utility class for reusability.

#### [NEW] [MobileNav.jsx](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/client/src/components/MobileNav.jsx)
- A fixed bottom navigation bar for mobile screens.
- Hidden on desktop (md+ screens).

#### [MODIFY] [Layout.jsx](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/client/src/components/Layout.jsx) (or App.jsx)
- Integrate `MobileNav` and adjust main content padding to prevent overlap.
- Apply the new background style globally.

#### [NEW] [ActivityChart.jsx](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/client/src/components/ActivityChart.jsx)
- Use `recharts` to display a bar chart of weekly activity.
- Mock data initially, then hook up to API if data exists.

#### [MODIFY] [Dashboard.jsx](file:///d:/project/Fittness%20tracking%20website/client/src/pages/Dashboard.jsx)
- Replace old stats with the new `ActivityChart` component.
- Apply glassmorphism cards to existing stat widgets.

## Verification Plan

### Manual Verification
1.  **Visual Inspection**: Open the app in browser (mobile and desktop views).
2.  **Navigation Testing**: Click all nav items in the new mobile bar and verify routing.
3.  **Chart Interaction**: Hover over chart bars to see tooltips.
4.  **Responsive Check**: Resize window to ensure layout adapts correctly (Mobile Nav <-> Desktop Nav).
